<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cruz Returns to Astros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- A day earlier than expected, Houston first base  
coach Jose Cruz returned to the Astros on Thursday night after 
treatment for an irregular heartbeat. 
</P>
<P>
	Cruz left the team after its May 9 game against the Montreal  
Expos to begin treatment. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm feeling a lot better and I would feel even better if we  
could have won tonight,'' Cruz said following an 8-5 loss to 
Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
	Manager Larry Dierker, who collapsed in the dugout Sunday,  
remains hospitalized following brain surgery Tuesday. He will need 
at least four weeks to recover. 
</P>
<P>
	``With Larry and Mac out, I just felt I needed to get back,''  
Cruz said. ``I'm taking less medication now, so I knew it was time 
to return.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
