<DOCNO> APW19990617.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-17 17:56:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Rangers Turn Triple Play </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Rangers turned their first triple play in 22  
years, and just the second since the franchise moved to Texas, on 
Thursday night against the New York Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
	With Tino Martinez on second and Paul O'Neill on first, Aaron  
Sele ran a full count on Chili Davis. Yankees manager Joe Torre 
sent the runners, and Davis hit a liner to second baseman Mark 
McLemore, who threw to shortstop Royce Clayton for the second out. 
</P>
<P>
	Clayton threw to first baseman Rafael Palmeiro to complete  
Texas' first triple play since Aug. 8, 1977 against Oakland. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the first triple play hit into by the Yankees since Steve  
Balboni lined into a 6-4-3 triple play against Baltimore on June 
15, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
	The Yankees haven't turned a triple play of their own since June  
3, 1968. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
