<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Queen's Horse Wins at Royal Ascot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ASCOT, England (AP) -- It may be the sport of kings, but it's  
Queen Elizabeth II who's in the winner's circle. 
</P>
<P>
	The 73-year-old monarch's horse Blueprint bested a field of 18  
in the Duke of Edinburgh stakes at the annual Royal Ascot meet 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The horse, a 4-1 favorite ridden by American Gary Stevens, won  
comfortably by 1 1/2 lengths to net its royal owner $27,659. 
</P>
<P>
	The queen beamed as she walked from the royal stand to the  
winner's enclosure. 
</P>
<P>
	Blueprint was the queen's first winner at Royal Ascot since  
1995, when Phantom Gold won the Ribblesdale Stakes. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
