<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-17 16:40:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Ratings Plunge 36 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The post-Michael Jordan era of the NBA Finals  
began with a thud when it comes to television ratings. 
</P>
<P>
	San Antonio's 89-77 win over the New York Knicks got an 11.5  
rating and 21 share on NBC Wednesday night, down 36 percent from 
the 18.0 rating and 32 share for last year's opener between 
Jordan's Bulls and the Utah Jazz. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the lowest rating for the opening game of the Finals  
since NBC began televising the NBA in the 1990-91 season. 
</P>
<P>
	The rating is the percentage of TV households in the United  
States tuned to a program, and each point represents 994,000 homes. 
The share is the percentage tuned to a program among televisions in 
use on at the time. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
