<HEADLINE> Teen-Ager Charged in Motel Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) -- A 17-year-old girl was charged  
Thursday with killing a man whose body was found stuffed under a 
motel room bed after two tourists spent the night on it. 
</P>
<P>
	The identity of the girl, who is from New York City, was not  
released because she is a juvenile. She got into an argument with 
Saul Hernandez, 64, in his room at the Burgundy Motor Inn on June 8 
and stabbed him to death, Atlantic County Prosecutor Jeffrey Blitz 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The two had just met, Blitz said. He would not say what the  
argument was about. 
</P>
<P>
	Hernandez's body lay undiscovered for two days, until two German  
tourists who rented Room 112 complained about the smell. They 
stayed overnight anyway, and they were moved to a different room 
the next day. 
</P>
<P>
	Housekeepers cleaned the room but couldn't eliminate the smell,  
prompting them to look under the bed, where the body was lodged in 
a wooden platform that supported the mattress and box spring. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
