<HEADLINE> 76ers Owner Hurt in Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEPTFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Philadelphia 76ers owner Pat Croce was  
injured Thursday in a motorcycle accident shortly after beginning a 
planned coast-to-coast trip. 
</P>
<P>
	Team spokesman Rob Wilson said Thursday evening that Croce was  
undergoing surgery at the University of Pennsylvania Medical Center 
in Philadelphia for multiple fractures of his left leg. 
</P>
<P>
	Hospital spokeswoman Roseann Thompson said he was listed in fair  
condition. 
</P>
<P>
	State Police said the accident happened at 4:36 p.m. on Route  
55. 
</P>
<P>
	Wilson said Croce had pulled over to the side of the road and  
another motorcycle hit him. He didn't know if that biker was part 
of Croce's group. Several motorcyclists had embarked on the trip 
together. 
</P>
<P>
	The bikers had just set out from Croce's Ocean City home on what  
they envisioned as a coast-to-coast trip lasting about a week. None 
of the group continued on the trip after the accident, Wilson said. 
  	   	
</P>
