<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Says He Accidentally Killed Wife </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- A man accused of stabbing his wife 44 times and  
dumping her body in a swimming pool told jurors he was sleepwalking 
at the time and never would have consciously harmed her. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's no way I could do that, not intentionally,'' Scott  
Falater testified Wednesday at his capital murder trial. ``I loved 
her.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Falater, 43, doesn't deny killing his wife and stashing the  
knife before police arrived. He claims to have no memory of the 
attack, which his attorneys say took place during a sleepwalking 
episode that lasted 45 to 50 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	Falater wept as he described a near-perfect marriage to his wife  
of 20 years, Yarmila, who was slain at their home in 1997. He said 
he adored his wife, a medical technician and basket weaver who gave 
up her medical career to stay home with their two children. 
</P>
<P>
	Asked by his attorney, Michael Kimerer, what his reaction would  
be if someone had told him he would stab his wife 44 times, Falater 
replied: ``You're out of your mind.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Falater dismissed the prosecution's suggestion that the couple's  
marriage was under strain. Several defense witnesses acknowledged 
that Mrs. Falater had complained about the demands of the Mormon 
Church, in which her husband was an enthusiastic member. 
</P>
<P>
	Falater, who was raised Catholic, noted that his wife also had  
converted to the faith and was active in church activities. 
</P>
<P>
	Falater, an electrical engineer, also denied being unfaithful to  
his wife, as the prosecution contends. His teen-age children 
testified their parents had a harmonious marriage that had never 
been marred by violence. 
</P>
<P>
	The prosecution contends Falater's sleepwalking claim is  
nonsense and that his actions were too deliberate to have been the 
work of a sleepwalker. 
</P>
<P>
	Neighbor Greg Koons testified he watched over his back-yard  
fence as Falater went inside to wash his hands, ordered his dog to 
lie down, then rolled his wife's body into the pool and held her 
head under water. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
