<HEADLINE> Schulman Named Priceline.com's COO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) -- Priceline.com Inc., the Internet travel  
company that allows consumers to name their price for airline 
tickets and hotel rooms, has named Daniel Schulman as its president 
and chief operating officer. 
</P>
<P>
	Schulman, 41, was most recently the president of AT&AMP;T Corp.'s  
consumer markets division. He will report to chairman Richard 
Braddock and will have broad responsibility for all of the 
company's operations, including technology, marketing and product 
development. 
</P>
<P>
	Schulman succeeds Jesse Fink, who is returning to Walker  
Digital, the intellectual property laboratory that invented 
priceline.com's patented pricing system. 
</P>
<P>
	In a separate announcement Thursday, AT&AMP;T Corp. said H. Eugene  
Lockhart would replace Schulman. 
</P>
<P>
	Lockhart is currently AT&AMP;T's executive vice president and chief  
marketing officer. 

  	   	
