<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Police: Man Kills Wife and Two Kids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- A man despondent after accidentally  
suffocating his wife killed their two young children and then took 
his own life, police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Jennifer Gilbert, 25, apparently allowed her husband, Michael,  
27, to asphyxiate her, but he did not mean to kill her, Police Lt. 
Craig Van Schyndle said. 
</P>
<P>
	``It appears activities between them were consensual to her  
death,'' Van Schyndle said. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities would not elaborate, citing the ``sensitivity of  
these deaths.'' Asked whether Mrs. Gilbert's death was sex-related, 
police would not comment. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities believe she died Sunday. Michael Gilbert, upset  
after his wife's death, killed 1-year-old Evangeline and 
2-month-old Ivan and then himself on Monday, Van Schyndle said. 
</P>
<P>
	The family's bodies were found Tuesday. The woman and the  
children died of asphyxiation, medical examiner Joe Grantham said. 
</P>
<P>
	Michael Gilbert apparently tried to commit suicide several ways  
in the 24 hours after killing his family. He died of carbon 
monoxide poisoning, drugs or alcohol or some combination, Van 
Schyndle said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
