<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Money Funds Fell in Latest Week / Money Market Funds  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Assets of the nation's retail money market  
mutual funds decreased by $2.23 billion to $864.56 billion, the 
Investment Company Institute said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Assets of taxable money market funds in the retail category  
decreased by $1.72 billion to $716.81 billion for the week ended 
Wednesday, the Washington-based mutual fund trade group said. 
Tax-exempt fund assets decreased by $513.3 million to $147.75 
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Assets of institutional money market fund decreased by $9.53  
billion to $589.21 billion for the same period. Among institutional 
funds, taxable money market fund assets decreased by $8.62 billion 
to $540.89 billion; assets of tax-exempt funds decreased by $909.5 
million to $48.32 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Total money market assets stood at $1.454 trillion for the week.  
</P>
<P>
	Assets for the previous week were revised to $1.466 trillion to  
reflect reporting errors and a change in the number of funds 
reporting. 
</P>
<P>
	The seven-day average yield on money market mutual funds rose in  
the week ended Tuesday to 4.31 percent from 4.29 percent the 
previous week, said IBC's Money Fund Report, a trade journal 
published in Ashland, Mass., by IBC Financial Data Inc. The 30-day 
average yield rose to 4.30 percent from 4.29 percent the previous 
week, IBC Financial Data said. 
</P>
<P>
	The seven-day compounded yield rose to 4.40 percent from 4.38  
percent the previous week, and the 30-day compounded yield was 
unchanged at 4.39 percent, IBC Financial Data said. 
</P>
<P>
	The average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was  
59 days, up from 58 days, IBC Financial Data said. 
</P>
<P>
	The online service bankrate.com said its survey of 100 leading  
commercial banks, savings and loan associations and savings banks 
in the nation's 10 largest markets showed the annual percentage 
yield available on money market accounts fell to 2.04 percent 
Wednesday from 2.07 percent the previous week. 
</P>
<P>
	The North Palm Beach, Fla.-based unit of Intelligent Life Corp.  
said the annual percentage yield available on interest-bearing 
checking accounts fell to 0.88 percent from 0.90 percent the 
previous week. 
</P>
<P>
	Bankrate.com said the annual percentage yield was 4.14 percent  
on six-month certificates of deposit, unchanged from the previous 
week. Yields were 4.45 percent on 1-year CDs, up from 4.44 percent; 
4.66 percent on 2 1/2-year CDs, up from 4.59 percent; and 4.81 percent 
on 5-year CDs, up from 4.77 percent. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
