<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Open Glance  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PINEHURST, N.C. (AP) -- A brief look at the first round of the  
U.S. Open, played on the 7,175-yard, par-70 Pinehurst No. 2 
course: 
</P>
<P>
	 *Leading:* David Duval, the world's top-ranked player, shot a  
3-under-par 67 and was tied for the lead with Phil Mickelson, Billy 
Mayfair and Paul Goydos. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Chasing:* Tiger Woods and John Daly were one shot off the lead.  
The group at 1-under included Vijay Singh, Justin Leonard, Jim 
Furyk and Hal Sutton. Davis Love fired a 70. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Key statistic:* The last time as many as four players were tied  
for the lead after the first round was 1984, when Mike Donald, 
Hubert Green, Hale Irwin and Jim Thorpe shot 2-under 68 at Winged 
Foot. Thorpe turned out to the highest finisher among that group, 
tying for fourth behind winner Fuzzy Zoeller, Greg Norman and 
Curtis Strange. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Note of the day:* Woods, ranked second in the world, and Duval  
each broke par in the opening round of a U.S. Open for the first 
time. Maybe they'll finally go head-to-head in a final round of a 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote of the day:* ``It's not worth the tournament,'' said  
Mickelson, vowing to return home if his pregnant wife, Amy, goes 
into labor. ``As important as the U.S. Open is to me and every 
other player in the field, this is the birth of my first child.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Key groups:* Duval, Mickelson, Carlos Franco (69), 11:50 a.m.;  
Woods, Lee Westwood (73) and Corey Pavin (74), 7:30 a.m.; Daly, 
Furyk and Darren Clarke (73), 8:30 a.m.; Leonard, Love and Greg 
Norman (73), 7:20 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Television (all times EDT):* Friday, Noon-3 p.m. (ESPN), 3-5  
p.m. (NBC), 5-7:30 p.m. (ESPN); Saturday and Sunday, 12:30-7 p.m. 
(NBC); Monday (if necessary), Noon-2 p.m. (ESPN), 2 p.m.-conclusion 
(NBC). 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
