<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed, Gold Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed today against other  
major currencies in late European trading. Gold prices fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar fell to 119.81 Japanese yen from 120.43 yen late  
Wednesday and was lower against the British pound but rose against 
the euro. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.5934, up from $1.5823, but  
the euro fell to $1.0305 from $1.0316 Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Wednesday 1.5493 Swiss  
francs, up from 1.5479, and 1.4588 Canadian dollars, up from 
1.4580. 
</P>
<P>
	At midday in New York, the dollar was trading at 119.68 yen and  
1.5440 Swiss francs. The British pound was quoted at $1.5920 while 
the euro was trading at $1.0328. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8979 German marks, up from 1.8959; 
6.3654 French francs, up from 6.3586; 2.1385 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.1362, and 1,878.96 Italian lire, up from 1,876.96. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $258.30 per troy ounce, down from  
$258.40 on Wednesday. In Zurich the bid was $258.15, down from 
$258.55. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed at $258.95 in Hong Kong, unchanged from late  
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.06 per troy ounce, up from $5.03.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
