<HEADLINE> Record Set in Challenge's 10th Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GLENNS FERRY, Idaho (AP) -- Zoulfija Zabirova of Lithuania, the  
Olympic time trial gold medalist, won the 76.7-mile 10th stage of 
the Women's Challenge bicycle race on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Zabirova finished Thursday's race in 3 hours, 15 seconds, nine  
seconds ahead of 1992 Olympic pursuit gold medalist Petra Rossner 
of Germany. 
</P>
