<HEADLINE> Lopez Not Abandoning Film Career </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Despite topping the charts,  
Jennifer Lopez says she hasn't abandoned the silver screen for the 
music business. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'll continue doing both, and I want to do both better,'' Ms.  
Lopez said. ``I really have a desire to keep striving and doing 
more.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Lopez's single ``If You Had My Love'' is No. 1 on  
Billboard's Hot 100 list. 
</P>
<P>
	During a visit Wednesday to her family's native Puerto Rico, Ms.  
Lopez said she will begin work on a thriller, ``The Cell,'' in July 
and plans to star in a romantic comedy, ``The Wedding Planner,'' 
next year. 
</P>
<P>
	Her movie credits include ``Selena,'' ``Money Train'' and ``Out  
of Sight.'' 
  	   	
