<HEADLINE> Minister Comments on Cox Marriage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Some might compare a Hollywood marriage  
to living in a fish bowl, but Courteney Cox's childhood minister 
believes hers will be different. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rev. Douglas Carpenter, who married Cox and David Arquette  
in San Francisco last weekend, said he compared the couple to ``a 
light on a hill.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``One of the things I said in my sermon is that so many people  
know them and will be looking at them,'' said Carpenter, pastor of 
St. Stephen's Episcopal Church in Cahaba Heights. 
</P>
<P>
	``If they see what a great marriage they have, it will help.  
Hollywood has a reputation of not taking marriage seriously, but 
these two are taking it seriously.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Cox, 35, star of TV's ``Friends,'' grew up in Mountain  
Brook, a suburb of Birmingham, and has known Carpenter since she 
was 10. Arquette, 27, is an actor best known for his role in the 
``Scream'' films. 
  	   	
