<HEADLINE> AP Names News Editor in D.C. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Laura A. Myers, a newswoman in the Washington  
bureau of The Associated Press, has been promoted to news editor 
for national security and international affairs. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced today by Chief of Bureau Sandy  
Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
	Myers joined the AP in Reno, Nev., in 1987. She also worked in  
the AP's San Francisco bureau and was correspondent in San Jose, 
Calif., until 1992, when she joined the Peace Corps in Africa. 
</P>
<P>
	Myers, 37, rejoined the AP in 1995 in Washington, where she has  
reported on politics, national security and international affairs. 
</P>
<P>
	She is a native of Las Vegas and a graduate of the University of  
Nevada-Reno. 
  	   	
</P>
