<HEADLINE> Football Star Jim Brown Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Hall of Fame football player and actor Jim  
Brown has been arrested on suspicion of threatening his wife. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown was taken into custody Tuesday evening after police got a  
call from his wife. He was freed on $50,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
	On Wednesday, Brown, 63, and his wife, Monique, 25, said outside  
their Hollywood Hills home that they are still together and are 
working out their differences. 
</P>
<P>
	``I did call 911. I kind of overreacted,'' Mrs. Brown said. ``In  
those situations, you get emotional and you're not thinking 
straight. I was in no harm. There was no threat towards me. And 
that's it.'' 
  	   	
