	Dow Gains 0.32, Nasdaq Gains 8  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Just before 2 p.m. EDT, the Dow Jones industrial  
average was up 0.32 at 10,785.27. NYSE advancers led decliners 
1,541-1,290. The Nasdaq composite index was up 8.15 at 2,525.98. 

</P>
<P>
	Duval, Mickelson Lead U.S. Open  
</P>
<P>
	PINEHURST, N.C. (AP) -- David Duval, the world's top-ranked  
golfer in search of his first major championship, shot a nearly 
flawless 3-under 67 in the rain at Pinehurst No. 2 today to tie 
playing partner Phil Mickelson for the early lead in the U.S. Open. 
Showing no ill effects from burns he suffered on his hand last 
week, Duval didn't make a bogey all day and birdied two of the last 
four holes to pull even with Mickelson and share the clubhouse 
lead. Mickelson, seeking his first major championship while 
anxiously awaiting the birth of his first child, made five birdies 
and made a 10-foot par putt on the last hole to retain his share of 
the lead. 

</P>
<P>
	Sabres, Stars Serve Up Cup Thrills  
</P>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- What's being considered a truly competitive series  
in the Stanley Cup playoffs goes into Game 5 tonight in Dallas with 
the hometown Stars and the Buffalo Sabres tied 2-2. The previous 
four seasons saw 4-0 sweeps in the finals. ``This is as tight a 
matchup as you'll find,'' Stars forward Brian Skrudland said. 
``Both teams deserve a lot of credit for where they are.'' 

</P>
