</P>
<P>
	PINEHURST, N.C. (AP) -- A soggy Pinehurst greeted golfers this  
morning as play began in the U.S. Open on a course soaked by 
overnight rains. Phil Mickelson, carrying a beeper to alert him if 
his pregnant wife began going into labor, made three birdies in his 
first five holes and held the early lead with about a third of the 
field on the course at 2-under after seven holes. Jack Nicklaus, 
playing in his first Open since having hip replacement surgery, 
bogeyed five of his first six holes, while Japan's Jumbo Ozaki took 
a quadruple bogey on the 11th hole and was 10-over through 13. 

</P>
