<HEADLINE> Dow Drops 53; Nasdaq Falls 17 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened lower. The Dow Jones  
Industrial Average is down 43 points in today's early going. Losers 
on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 3-2 lead over gainers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is down 17 points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is down four points. 
</P>
<P>
	Stocks are beginning today's session with a nasty earnings  
warning from one of the big high-tech companies. 
</P>
<P>
	Compaq says it's expecting a loss of up to 15 cents a share in  
the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts had been expecting a gain of 29 cents a share.  
</P>
