<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Redskins Sign Offensive Tackle Heck </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Offensive tackle Andy Heck, cut by Chicago  
this month, has signed a one-year, $450,000 contract with the 
Washington Redskins. 
</P>
<P>
	Heck, whose contract includes a $150,000 signing bonus, is  
entering his 11th NFL season. He was the first-round pick by 
Seattle in the 1989 draft and went on to spend his first four 
seasons with the Seahawks. 
</P>
<P>
	Heck (6-6, 298) signed with Chicago prior to the 1994 season. He  
has started 76 of 80 games at left tackle for the Bears. Last 
season, he started 14 games with Chicago, missing two weeks because 
of a broken big toe and was cut by the Bears in a salary cap move. 
</P>
<P>
	Heck has played in 153 games and 146 starts in his career.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
