<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Deutsche Bank Officials Probed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) -- German authorities investigating  
allegations that Deutsche Bank helped customers evade taxes is now 
examining the role of some of the bank's top officials, including 
Chairman Rolf Breuer, the Frankfurt prosecutor's office said. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators have been probing for a year whether employees of  
Deutsche Bank regularly helped customers funnel money into accounts 
in Luxembourg and elsewhere to avoid a withholding tax on interest 
income. 
</P>
<P>
	While Breuer and other members of the board were not suspected  
of involvement in actual transfer of money, they bore final 
responsibility for the operations, prosecutor spokesman Job Tilmann 
said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Deutsche Bank acknowledged that three other board members were  
being investigated. Two former board members were also under 
investigation. 
</P>
<P>
	Tilmann said prosecutors believe the transfers to avoid taxes  
were ``a widespread practice'' involving many customers. 
</P>
<P>
	Deutsche Bank became the world's largest bank after its recent  
merger with U.S.-based Bankers Trust. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors started investigating German banks as early as 1994  
for helping customers avoid taxes on earned interest imposed under 
a 1992 law. As the investigations progressed, bank customers 
involved in the scheme were encouraged to turn themselves in and 
make back payments to avoid proescution. 
</P>
<P>
	According to Tilmann, about 400 Deutsche Bank customers have  
given information on money transfers they say bank employees helped 
them with to avoid taxes, and about 100 bank employees have 
admitted their part. 
</P>
<P>
	Deutsche Bank denies wrongdoing, saying individual customers are  
responsible for declaring their income. 
</P>
<P>
	``We have more than 6 million customers,'' Deutsche Bank  
spokesman Dierk Hartwig said. ``We're not in a position to know 
what they do as private taxpayers.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
