<HEADLINE> Circus Circus Shareholders OK Name </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Shareholders of Circus Circus Enterprises Inc.  
on Thursday approved changing the company's name to Mandalay Resort 
Group. 
</P>
<P>
	The company will begin trading on the New York Stock Exchange  
Monday under a new symbol, MBG. 
</P>
<P>
	The new name was taken from the Mandalay Bay resort, which  
opened on the Las Vegas Strip in March. 
</P>
<P>
	The company owns and operates 11 properties in Nevada, including  
five on the Strip. It also has a hotel-casino in Mississippi and 
owns a half interest in a riverboat casino in Illinois. 
</P>
<P>
	Circus Circus also plans to develop a $65 million time-share  
resort near the Oriental-themed Mandalay Bay, company spokeswoman 
Sarah Ralston said. 
</P>
<P>
	Shares of Circus Circus closed Thursday up nearly 6 percent, or  
$1.25, at $22.18 3/4. 


  	   	
</P>
