<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-17 15:00:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Catinca Looks To Increase Respect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Catinca gets another chance to prove she is  
among the best fillies and mares around in Saturday's Hempstead 
Handicap at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	A win in the 1 1-16th-mile race would be her eighth victory in  
10 career starts. 
</P>
<P>
	``She's starting to get the respect she deserves,'' trainer John  
Kimmel said Thursday. ``If she's going to be mentioned in the same 
breath as the best fillies and mares in the country, she's got to 
win races like these.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In her last start, Catinca came off a fast pace to win the  
one-mile Shuvee. There's more likely to be a slower pace on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	``If they go slower, she'll be closer,'' jockey Richard Migliore  
said. ``She's a filly with a lot of natural speed. I think she's 
better if she makes one run. She's the kind of horse you have to 
get to settle. 
</P>
<P>
	``The only unknown now is going a sixteenth of a mile farther.  
She gets the mile real well. I can't imagine the extra sixteenth 
being a problem, but you don't know until you've done it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Catinca will carry 122 pounds in the $250,000 test for fillies  
and mares and spot five rivals from five to eight pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Also entered are Sister Act, 117; Furlough, 114; Snit, 113;  
Beautiful Pleasure, 112, and Let, 111. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
