<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Globe Available to Blind People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- The Boston Globe announced Thursday the newspaper  
will be available to blind people in Massachusetts through a 
service provided by the Massachusetts Association for the Blind. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcement marks the first time the contents of a daily  
newspaper will be available for the state's approximately 100,000 
blind and partially sighted people. 
</P>
<P>
	Using a touch-tone telephone, callers can dial a local number  
and choose a newspaper, a section and an article from a list of 
options. The current day's issue, the previous day's and the 
previous Sunday's paper are available. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
