<HEADLINE> Fox's Hill Gets More Global Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Fox Sports head David Hill will assume a more  
global role following his promotion Thursday to chairman and chief 
executive officer of the Fox Sports Television Group. 
</P>
<P>
	Hill, 53, will oversee all of News Corp.'s global sports media,  
including Sky Sports, ESPN Star Sports and TM3. He had spent the 
past two years as chairman and CEO of Fox Broadcasting Co. 
</P>
<P>
	Hill will continue to report to Peter Chernin, president and  
chief operating officer of Fox Entertainment Group, and Chase 
Carey, the co-COO. 
</P>
<P>
	Jeff Shell will become president of Fox Sports Networks, in  
charge of cable programming, distribution and ad sales. He had been 
executive vice president and chief financial officer of Fox Sports 
Net. 
</P>
<P>
	News Corp. owns 82 percent of Fox Entertainment Group Inc.  

</P>
</TEXT>
