<HEADLINE> Jackals Activate Mark Lemke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LITTLE FALLS, N.J. (AP) -- Former major league infielder Mark  
Lemke was taken off the disabled list Wednesday by the New Jersey 
Jackals, moving him a step closer to making his debut as a 
knuckleball pitcher. 
</P>
<P>
	Lemke, 33, was placed on the disabled list a week ago with a  
sore right arm. He has doubled as an infield coach while working on 
his pitching. 
</P>
<P>
	The Jackals are in the independent Northern League.  
  	   	
</P>
